<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-162] 31.2.6. Watching the OST Block I/O Stream</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-162</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the June 2013 manual there is this heading:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;31.2.6. Watching the OST Block I/O Stream&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when referring to the brw_stats file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Elsewhere I have seen &quot;brw&quot; referred to as &quot;bulk read write&quot; as opposed to &quot;block read write&quot; - I don&apos;t know the history, but presumably after going from blocks (ext3) to extents (ext4) this subtle change was introduced.  If, in fact, this file is now called &quot;bulk read write&quot;, this and any other references to &quot;block&quot; should be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
